  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined by law as the process of concealing the origin of illegally obtained money, typically by means of transfers involving foreign banks or legitimate businesses. Key elements include:\n\n1. Placement - Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering - Conducting complex financial transactions to obscure the money's source\n3. Integration - Making illegally obtained money appear legitimate\n\nSpecific criminal activities can include:\n- Transferring funds from illegal sources\n- Disguising the origin of criminal proceeds\n- Structuring transactions to avoid reporting requirements\n- Using shell companies or offshore accounts\n\nExact legal definitions can vary by jurisdiction, but most countries have laws criminalizing these activities.\n\nWould you like me to provide more general information about money laundering laws?",
